    Title: Early Journals
Title: With Each Thing
---
Who can say what is? Who is able to judge the true worth of things?

I can only measure the world in terms of longing. All things are so ready to
accommodate our many and often mistaken thoughts and wishes. With each thing I
would like to rest for a night, after a day of "doing" with other things. I
would like to sleep once with each thing, nestled in its warmth; to dream in
the rhythm of its breathing, its dear, naked neighborliness against my limbs,
and grow strong in the fragrance of its sleep. Then, early in the morning,
before it awakens, before any good-byes, to move on, to move on ...
